Outputs data to the standard output stream.
```cpp
std::cout << "Hello World" << std::endl;
std::cout << "x = " << x << ", y = " << y << '\n';
```

Reads formatted input from standard input.
```cpp
int n;
std::string name;
std::cin >> n >> name;
```

Sorts elements in the range `[first, last)` in ascending order (or by `comp`).
```cpp
std::sort(vec.begin(), vec.end());
std::sort(arr, arr + n, std::greater<int>());
std::sort(v.begin(), v.end(), [](int a, int b) { return a > b; });
```

Searches for the first element equal to `value` in `[first, last)`.
```cpp
auto it = std::find(vec.begin(), vec.end(), 42);
if (it != vec.end()) { /* found */ }
```

Applies `op` to each element in `[first, last)` and stores in `result`.
```cpp
std::transform(v.begin(), v.end(), v.begin(), [](int x) { return x * 2; });
std::transform(a.begin(), a.end(), b.begin(), c.begin(), std::plus<>());
```

Appends a copy of `value` to the end of the vector.
```cpp
std::vector<int> v;
v.push_back(42);
v.push_back(100);
```

Constructs an element in-place at the end of the vector.
```cpp
std::vector<std::pair<int,int>> v;
v.emplace_back(1, 2);
```

Creates a `shared_ptr` managing a new object of type `T`.
```cpp
auto ptr = std::make_shared<MyClass>(arg1, arg2);
auto sp = std::make_shared<int>(42);
```

Creates a `unique_ptr` managing a new object of type `T` (C++14+).
```cpp
auto ptr = std::make_unique<MyClass>(arg1, arg2);
auto up = std::make_unique<int[]>(10);
```
